       inverse of that tilt (to level the sensor: z world-up, scan plane horizontal) COMPOSED WITH a +45deg
       yaw about the (level) z axis. The yaw re-centers the 270deg sweep so that the 90deg blind notch tucks
       into the back-right chassis corner (the sensor sits at the front-left corner): beam-0 -> base-yaw -90deg
       (grazing along the front edge), beam-90 -> base-yaw 180deg (grazing along the left edge), and the fan
       opens outward to the front-left. Without the yaw the fan was centered on +X and swept rearward across
       the robot's own body, so ~1/4 of the beams self-hit. Net body quat = inv(tilt) * Rot_Z(+45deg)
       = "0 0.707107 -0.707107 0". Each site still follows the picknik_mujoco_ros convention
       R_site(i) = Rot_Z(phi + i*3deg) * Rot_Y(+90deg); the +45deg body yaw shifts the effective phi by +45deg.
       Rangefinders use angle_min=0, so the plugin publishes a z-up lidar_front_ROS frame whose X axis points
       at beam-0 (rotated with the sites, so the scan stays self-consistent). NOTE: <replicate> is intentionally
       NOT used (known issue in this pipeline); sites are enumerated explicitly with one <rangefinder> per beam
       in sensor.xml.
